WEBVTT

00:01.762 --> 00:04.745
Welcome to the podcast for Perdido Bay Methodist Church.

00:04.865 --> 00:05.866
My name is Dudley.

00:06.687 --> 00:13.494
And today is Monday, March 9th, where we're reading Matthew 24, verses 36 through 51.

00:13.534 --> 00:17.358
And we are told to be watchful.

00:18.139 --> 00:22.583
This passage says that in the days of Noah, people were just living life.

00:23.544 --> 00:29.330
And we know that in that day, people were not following God because the flood soon followed.

00:29.570 --> 00:31.713
they were serving their own selves.

00:32.634 --> 00:40.926
Genesis 6, 11 says that these people were a people of violence and that the earth had become corrupt.

00:41.928 --> 00:43.470
And there was a progression.

00:43.510 --> 00:46.554
There's always a progression to sin.

00:46.614 --> 00:57.650
Like in Psalm 1, when the righteous and the wicked are contrasted, the righteous love God's word and they see God's blessings and benefits, but the wicked

00:57.858 --> 01:02.582
They follow a downward spiral, a progression of destruction.

01:03.663 --> 01:11.391
First, they're walking in the council of the wicked, and then it seems that they slow down and they stand in the pathway of the sinners.

01:11.811 --> 01:15.515
And finally, they are sitting in the seat of scoffers.

01:16.315 --> 01:24.263
Now, this is a negative progression, and it's their response to what God has said.

01:24.683 --> 01:26.125
It's like they're walking the wrong way.

01:26.505 --> 01:27.506
Then they stop.

01:27.586 --> 01:28.447
And then they sit.

01:29.288 --> 01:35.215
The progression is one of intimacy and fellowship, but in the wrong direction.

01:35.796 --> 01:40.342
They are fellowshiping in the ways of wickedness.

01:40.982 --> 01:44.887
The righteous, however, live God's word out, and they see the benefit.

01:44.967 --> 01:46.029
They love God's word.

01:46.069 --> 01:47.490
They see the wisdom.

01:47.530 --> 01:50.294
They desire to fellowship and commune with God.

01:50.334 --> 01:53.778
The difference between the righteous and the wicked

01:54.114 --> 01:57.678
is their view and their response to the word of God.

01:58.539 --> 02:07.909
So it's important to realize that our minds are shaped by the words that we listen to, either God's word or the words of the world.

02:09.051 --> 02:17.460
Like in the garden, Adam and Eve valued the word of the snake more than the words of God and it affected everything.

02:17.840 --> 02:22.866
We are still wrestling with sin because it was introduced on that very day.

02:23.970 --> 02:29.355
God said to man and woman on that day that they could eat from any tree, except for the one.

02:29.675 --> 02:32.238
His words were good, the best, actually.

02:32.778 --> 02:37.563
And the word of the serpent went directly against what God had said.

02:37.603 --> 02:49.514
So the issues and sins that mankind deal with come when we don't listen to the one who loves us the most, the one who wants the best for us.

02:50.555 --> 02:53.298
So in the days of Noah and in the end times,

02:53.730 --> 02:58.537
They knew nothing about what would happen until the flood came and took them all away.

02:59.419 --> 03:02.744
That is how it will be at the coming of the Son of Man.

03:03.525 --> 03:07.351
Two men will be in the field, one will be taken, and the other left.

03:07.551 --> 03:13.200
Two women will be grinding with a hand mill, one will be taken, and the other left.

03:13.740 --> 03:18.888
Therefore, keep watch because you do not know on what day your Lord will come.

03:19.990 --> 03:22.674
And the scripture passage goes on to say,

03:22.786 --> 03:32.457
who then is the faithful and wise servant whom the Master has put in charge of the servants in his household to give them their food at the proper time.

03:33.358 --> 03:38.464
It will be good for that servant whose Master finds him doing so when he returns.

03:39.986 --> 03:50.898
So it will be important for us to be listening to God and following the assignment that he has for us when he returns because he's coming back one day.

03:51.394 --> 03:58.424
the wise and faithful servants of God hear his words and walk in relationship and communion with him.

03:58.905 --> 04:11.462
And they see the value of the assignment that they are given that we ourselves are not only being saved, but we can, through God's power, make an impact in this world.

04:12.844 --> 04:14.927
You'll see there's two things going on here.

04:15.348 --> 04:19.794
There's the inner life of love and devotion, of relationship with God.

04:20.066 --> 04:24.712
and this comes first, and then there's the assignment that God has given us.

04:25.132 --> 04:35.244
He's gifted each one of us with varying gifts and abilities, and he's given us spiritual gifts to make great and eternal impact.

04:36.125 --> 04:46.738
As we ponder these things today, let's agree to allow God's words to draw us closer to Him in relationship, to abide in Him, and then to be astounded

04:46.978 --> 04:52.645
and amazed that He can take our lives and do something that matters for eternity.

04:53.165 --> 05:01.055
He can use us to lead others to Jesus to that salvation that only He can provide.

05:01.916 --> 05:08.223
He can reveal His love and salvation to those around us as we walk out our daily lives.

05:09.805 --> 05:10.706
Have a blessed day.

